<paragraph id="76FCF292FA4761DEAFC0213FFB33F32E" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">
Maximum length: ♂ 2.2 mm, ♀ 3.5 mm. Dorsal surface slightly granulated, granules on pereonites 1-7 in two transverse rows, pleon smooth (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D3E5F37839466E306D4AA41A546B8242" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Pectenoniscus pankaru Campos-Filho, Torres &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♀, LES 27763) A habitus, dorsal view B habitus, lateral view C cephalon, dorsal view. Pectenoniscus fervens Campos-Filho, Taiti &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♀, LES 27764) D habitus, dorsal view E habitus, lateral view F cephalon, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684902" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">4A, B</figureCitation>
). Dorsal scale-setae tricorn-shaped (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="682B69D88C41EFDF30DF3C55911D8763" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Pectenoniscus pankaru Campos-Filho, Torres &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♂, LES 27762) A dorsal scale-seta B cephalon, frontal view C pleonites 4, 5 and telson D antennula E antenna F left mandible G right mandible H maxillula I maxilla J maxilliped." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684903" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">5A</figureCitation>
). Cephalon (Figs 
<figureCitation id="3217B6452D846D50B6AE450F62CFF301" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Pectenoniscus pankaru Campos-Filho, Torres &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♀, LES 27763) A habitus, dorsal view B habitus, lateral view C cephalon, dorsal view. Pectenoniscus fervens Campos-Filho, Taiti &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♀, LES 27764) D habitus, dorsal view E habitus, lateral view F cephalon, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684902" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">4C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="EE956B0CD3DD1A580235E7A7248CD618" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Pectenoniscus pankaru Campos-Filho, Torres &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♂, LES 27762) A dorsal scale-seta B cephalon, frontal view C pleonites 4, 5 and telson D antennula E antenna F left mandible G right mandible H maxillula I maxilla J maxilliped." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684903" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">5B</figureCitation>
) with well-developed quadrangular antennary lobes, slightly directed outwards; profrons with suprantennal line bent downwards medially. Pereonite 1-3 epimera with postero-lateral corners right-angled, 4-7 progressively more acute and directed backwards; pleonite 5 epimera with glandular pores at sides near distal margins (Figs 
<figureCitation id="A0553D81D38D5DE94160E9D6C148B629" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Pectenoniscus pankaru Campos-Filho, Torres &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♀, LES 27763) A habitus, dorsal view B habitus, lateral view C cephalon, dorsal view. Pectenoniscus fervens Campos-Filho, Taiti &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♀, LES 27764) D habitus, dorsal view E habitus, lateral view F cephalon, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684902" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">4A, B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="C510164D40DC7781F60807691BA5325F" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Pectenoniscus pankaru Campos-Filho, Torres &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♂, LES 27762) A dorsal scale-seta B cephalon, frontal view C pleonites 4, 5 and telson D antennula E antenna F left mandible G right mandible H maxillula I maxilla J maxilliped." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684903" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">5C</figureCitation>
). Telson (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="97B9B20232AFA5D7B629E9E5700AB19A" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Pectenoniscus pankaru Campos-Filho, Torres &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♂, LES 27762) A dorsal scale-seta B cephalon, frontal view C pleonites 4, 5 and telson D antennula E antenna F left mandible G right mandible H maxillula I maxilla J maxilliped." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684903" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">5C</figureCitation>
) almost three times as wide as long, with concave sides and rounded apex. Antennula (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1B807758028B1E98C46A08A89D366331" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Pectenoniscus pankaru Campos-Filho, Torres &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♂, LES 27762) A dorsal scale-seta B cephalon, frontal view C pleonites 4, 5 and telson D antennula E antenna F left mandible G right mandible H maxillula I maxilla J maxilliped." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684903" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">5D</figureCitation>
) with distal article longer than second and first, and bearing at least 12 aesthetascs. Antenna (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="70F3A4C9CEEB9D1B9BCEBC5EDAAD7698" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Pectenoniscus pankaru Campos-Filho, Torres &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♂, LES 27762) A dorsal scale-seta B cephalon, frontal view C pleonites 4, 5 and telson D antennula E antenna F left mandible G right mandible H maxillula I maxilla J maxilliped." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684903" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">5E</figureCitation>
) with fifth article of peduncle as long as flagellum, bearing one distal strong seta; flagellum of four articles, first article longest, apical organ as long as distal article of flagellum. Mandibles as in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="23A9BB8193DD4C6A4AAE98DB27C11045" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Pectenoniscus pankaru Campos-Filho, Torres &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♂, LES 27762) A dorsal scale-seta B cephalon, frontal view C pleonites 4, 5 and telson D antennula E antenna F left mandible G right mandible H maxillula I maxilla J maxilliped." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684903" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">5F, G</figureCitation>
, right mandible with leaf-like lacinia mobilis. Maxillula (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B43C19D5E54357102250B0A7A9082C78" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Pectenoniscus pankaru Campos-Filho, Torres &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♂, LES 27762) A dorsal scale-seta B cephalon, frontal view C pleonites 4, 5 and telson D antennula E antenna F left mandible G right mandible H maxillula I maxilla J maxilliped." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684903" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">5H</figureCitation>
) with two robust penicils; outer endite with 4+5 teeth, apically simple, one subapical slender stalk near medial margin. Maxilla as in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9F840BA6B5317578D1B5BDCE3D7852CC" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Pectenoniscus pankaru Campos-Filho, Torres &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♂, LES 27762) A dorsal scale-seta B cephalon, frontal view C pleonites 4, 5 and telson D antennula E antenna F left mandible G right mandible H maxillula I maxilla J maxilliped." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684903" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">5I</figureCitation>
. Maxilliped (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8956337D983E69D07B814BD1CF8FB7AB" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Pectenoniscus pankaru Campos-Filho, Torres &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♂, LES 27762) A dorsal scale-seta B cephalon, frontal view C pleonites 4, 5 and telson D antennula E antenna F left mandible G right mandible H maxillula I maxilla J maxilliped." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684903" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">5J</figureCitation>
) basis with lateral sides fringed with fine setae; palp with first article bearing two setae, distal articles fused and bearing many setae on lateral margins; endite much longer than wide, lateral margins covered with fine setae, distal margin bearing two strong setae and one elongated penicil. Grooves and scales for water conducting system on ischium, merus, carpus and propodus of pereopod 6 and basis of pereopod 7 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="FE31132CA8CD76CAB807E6BD4A2E2B0F" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Pectenoniscus pankaru Campos-Filho, Torres &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♂, LES 27762) A uropod B pereopod 1 C pereopod 7 D genital papila and pleopod 1 E pleopod 2 F pleopod 5 exopod." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684904" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">6C</figureCitation>
). Dactylus with ungual seta simple and dactylar seta bifid and setose. Uropod (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="74ABA750819A84A9BDE603BEA41BFE2D" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Pectenoniscus pankaru Campos-Filho, Torres &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♂, LES 27762) A uropod B pereopod 1 C pereopod 7 D genital papila and pleopod 1 E pleopod 2 F pleopod 5 exopod." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684904" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">6A</figureCitation>
) protopod and exopod grooved on outer margins bearing glandular pores; exopod longer than endopod, endopod inserted proximally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D47B7CFFC712D6601CC2CFC4283FDBF1" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="CE7965745E3EE6CC8EF7510AFC2A6A60" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Male.</emphasis>
Pereopods 1-6 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BDEFEF95BF5C444568665089E9656D59" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Pectenoniscus pankaru Campos-Filho, Torres &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♂, LES 27762) A uropod B pereopod 1 C pereopod 7 D genital papila and pleopod 1 E pleopod 2 F pleopod 5 exopod." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684904" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">6B</figureCitation>
) without any sexual modifications. Pereopod 7 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A1131B8FC951070B11AC50BB99940D3E" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Pectenoniscus pankaru Campos-Filho, Torres &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♂, LES 27762) A uropod B pereopod 1 C pereopod 7 D genital papila and pleopod 1 E pleopod 2 F pleopod 5 exopod." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684904" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">6C</figureCitation>
) propodus with brush of setae on rostral margin. Genital papilla (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F38950F71A9FCD4DD0666F2CC889D67B" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Pectenoniscus pankaru Campos-Filho, Torres &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♂, LES 27762) A uropod B pereopod 1 C pereopod 7 D genital papila and pleopod 1 E pleopod 2 F pleopod 5 exopod." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684904" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">6D</figureCitation>
) enlarged on median portion, apical part narrow and elongated. Pleopod 1 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="DB3A7C293B90FDCDD65C6EB46AB000FC" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Pectenoniscus pankaru Campos-Filho, Torres &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♂, LES 27762) A uropod B pereopod 1 C pereopod 7 D genital papila and pleopod 1 E pleopod 2 F pleopod 5 exopod." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684904" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">6D</figureCitation>
) protopod subrectangular, distal margin sinuous; exopod subtriangular, outer margin almost straight, proximal and outer margins convex; endopod longer than exopod, basal article short, distal article three times longer than basal one. Pleopod 2 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="24F25BC9D4AF706F329B507969839107" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Pectenoniscus pankaru Campos-Filho, Torres &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♂, LES 27762) A uropod B pereopod 1 C pereopod 7 D genital papila and pleopod 1 E pleopod 2 F pleopod 5 exopod." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684904" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">6E</figureCitation>
) exopod ovoid, more than three times as wide as long; endopod of two articles, thickset, second article more than twice as long as first, distally bearing round shaped lobe directed outwards. Pleopod 5 exopod (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="038173A4C3D2821AC8FAD1EA62EFED07" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Pectenoniscus pankaru Campos-Filho, Torres &amp; Bichuette, sp. nov. (♂, LES 27762) A uropod B pereopod 1 C pereopod 7 D genital papila and pleopod 1 E pleopod 2 F pleopod 5 exopod." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684904" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">6F</figureCitation>
) subquadrangular, slightly wider than long, bearing three setae, distal margin rounded.
</paragraph>
<caption id="D9D3B3A42DC58AD05A9D835DF0EECC6A" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1101.79043.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/684902" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" start="Figure 4" startId="F4">
