<subSubSection id="C653CA945E1A767D07915E799AF9C25E" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="0A708E13EE0B3BF2077BF5C8E3DF5F99" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="51C7695D1B11B15DF2FFA134403E9D8C" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">The new species is named for the indigenous people Pankaru, who inhabited the northern portion of Serra do Ramalho region.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9FF2E63419F5B6545767E613049A0C42" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="3AECC6F52FCF550C24A39033EE1EE052" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E2A622CD92D5CC1729AB5EB8856AF40B" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">
<taxonomicName id="40A7AC82EFE6556950BB367297906BD6" authorityName="Campos-Filho, Torres &amp; Bichuette" authorityYear="2022" class="Malacostraca" family="Styloniscidae " genus="Pectenoniscus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pectenoniscus pankaru" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pankaru">
<emphasis id="62910F07239E0E34AA7DAE8ABFF4C717" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Pectenoniscus pankaru</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. differs from all other species of the genus in the shape of the male pleopod 2 endopod. Moreover, it differs in having the antennal flagellum composed of four articles (vs. five in 
<taxonomicName id="9F85BCE3B7E688577E0D042B986AEC0C" genus="P." lsidName="P. angulatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" rank="species" species="angulatus">
<emphasis id="B7E980F476459024799D816D0BFC9741" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">P. angulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, three in 
<taxonomicName id="25F2F93165921EF97596D8C609F1B131" genus="P." lsidName="P. carinhanhensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" rank="species" species="carinhanhensis">
<emphasis id="1B9D2321B17773AA890B1B12D80B98B0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">P. carinhanhensis</emphasis>
